Preheat your oven to 220°C. Pop your @pizza bases{2} on a large #baking tray{}. Drain the @mozzarella{1} and pull apart into small pieces. Mix the @tomato puree{60} and @green pesto{45} in a small #bowl{}. Divide the tomato puree mixture between your pizzas. Use a #spoon{} to spread it out over the bases, leaving a 2cm border.

Scatter the mozzarella evenly between your pizza bases. Bake in your oven until the cheese is golden and bubbly, ~{12-14%minutes}.

Meanwhile, put the @balsamic vinegar{12} in a large bowl and add the @olive oil{1%for the dressing}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir together with a #fork{}. Halve the @premium tomato mix{125} and pop them in the bowl with the dressing, toss to combine, leave to the side. Trim the root from the @wild rocket{40} then separate the leaves.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium high heat. When hot, add the @sliced mushrooms{150} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir fry until the mushrooms are golden brown, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add the garlic, stir and cook for ~{1%minute}. Remove the pan from the heat.

Once the pizza is cooked, remove from the oven. Share the garlic mushrooms between the pizzas.

Toss the baby gem leaves through the bowl with the tomatoes and dressing. Serve alongside the pizzas (or on top if you prefer!) Enjoy!